article.headline: Illinois State 85, Lewis 66
article.story: NORMAL, Ill. (AP) -- Anthony Slack and Boo Richardson combined to score nearly half of Illinois State's points in an 85-66 win over Lewis on Tuesday night. Slack scored 22 points for the Redbirds (7-4) on 8-for-9 shooting from the field and 6-for-7 free-throw shooting before fouling out with 6:45 to go in the game. Richardson was 8-for-11 overall, including three 3-pointers, to finish with 20 points. Lewis (5-5) was led by Brandon Dagans' 25 points, 11 of which came during a perfect performance from the free-throw line. Dagans also hit four 3-pointers in the game. Matthew Marino was the only other Flyers player in double figures, scoring 10. Illinois State shot nearly 52 percent in the first half, taking a 47-36 lead at the break, and 56 percent in the second. Lewis turned the ball over 28 times.
